The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) has partnered with the National Human Rights Commission (NHRC) to create conducive environment for people to enjoy their rights without discrimination.  The State Commandant of the Corps, Alhaji Modu Bunu disclosed this in a statement issued after a delegation from the NHRC led by Mr. Terngu Gwar paid him a courtesy visit.   Earlier in his remark, leader of the delegation and Chief Research Officer, Terngu Gwar, explained that the call was aimed at seeking NSCDC partnership to advance the course of human rights promotion, protection and enforcement in the State. 